<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-070 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  11 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spring Friendship Art Festival Opens </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spring Friendship Art Festival Opens </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Performances Reported </H4>

<F P=102> SK1104115494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1135 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1104115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Foreign artistes and 
Korean artistes overseas participating in the 12th April Spring 
Friendship Art Festival gave their premiere before full houses 
at the Mansudae Art Theatre, the February 8 House of Culture, 
the Ponghwa Art Theatre, the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre and 
other theatres in Pyongyang Sunday, separated into several 
groups. 
  The colorful program of the festival, which began at a time 
when the birthday of the great leader President Kim Il-song was 
significantly being celebrated, include songs, dances and 
instrumental music. 
  Participating in the current festival are more than 100 
international and domestic contest prize winners and other 
famous actors and actresses and many art troupes and artistes 
who have participated in the art festival on several occasions 
to become intimate with the Korean people. 
  Foreign artistes put on the stage songs written and composed 
by themselves in praise of the great leader President Kim 
Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il and Korean 
songs, delighting Korean people celebrating the holiday. 
  The Bangladeshi artistes sang "Song of Praise to the Great 
Leader" they had long prepared for the Pyongyang festival, 
winning the acclamation of the audience. 
  The trio of the Congo sang the song "Happiness of Mankind" 
reflecting the ardent desire of the world revolutionary people 
to always revere President Kim Il-song as the sun of mankind 
together with the Korean people, though they are different 
nations and have different languages and colors. 
  A Cuban vocal soloist Mario Travieso, a domestic contest 
prize winner, sang in Korean the Korean song "Good Health and 
Long Life to the Leader" and Mongolian artistes Korean songs "It 
Is Snowing" and "Soil and Soldier" in Korean, deeply impressing 
the audience. 
  Head of a delegation of the Japan-Korea music and art 
interchange society Mitsuko Ogasawara who has participated in 
the festival on several occasions to be well known to the Korean 
people sang the Korean song "We Will Go Together, Singing of 
Joy" to be applauded by the audience. 
  N.A. Tlendiev, the conductor of the Kazakh art troupe and 
former people's actor of the Soviet Union, in the orchestral 
music "Thought of Comrade Kim Il-song" he wrote and composed 
after reading the reminiscences of the great leader "With the 
Century", emotionally presented his idea of "Believing in the 
People as in Heaven." 
  Artistes from China, Russia, Cambodia, Yugoslavia, France, 
Nigeria, Malaysia, the Netherlands, Switzerland, and other 
countries put on the stage songs and dances reflecting the 
customs of their peoples. 
  Korean artistes overseas, happy to be embraced in the bosom 
of the great father, the homeland, ardently sang of their 
reverence for the respected leader President Kim Il-song. 
  China-resident Korean artistes in a narrative and song "Let 
Us Sing of Fortune in Having the Sagacious Leaders" sang of the 
Korean nation's pride and happiness in having President Kim 
Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il and enjoying good luck, to be 
enthusiastically applauded by the audience. 
  The festival continues. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

