<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Evening of Working People' Held 9 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Evening of Working People' Held 9 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1004095794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0859 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1004095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 10 (KCNA) -- An evening of working 
people on Pyongyang was held at the Kim Il-song Square Saturday 
to celebrate the 1st anniversary of the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il's election as chairman of the National Defence 
Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
  The evening was overflowing with deepest respect and 
reverence for General Kim Chong-il, supreme commander, always 
leading the Korean people and People's Army to victory, exalting 
the dignity and honour of the fatherland and nation with his 
rare military wisdom and prominent commanding art. The evening 
was a sea of beautiful flowers and dances. 
  With a solemn chorus of the song "We Will Win Because You 
Are 
Leading Us" all the participants of the evening sang and danced, 
renewing the faith that they are afraid of no formidable enemy 
and will certainly win as long as they are guided by General Kim 
Chong-il possessed of outstanding military wisdom and matchless 
grit. 

</TEXT>

