<H3> <TI>   National Photo Exhibition Opens in Pyongyang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Photo Exhibition Opens in Pyongyang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0904054294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0420 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0904054294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- A national photo 
exhibition opened at the People's Palace of Culture in Pyongyang 
Friday to celebrate the 15th of April. 
  On display there are about 80 pictures showing the deep 
respect and reverence of the Korean people and the world's 
progressive people for President Kim Il-song. Among them are 
the pictures "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il-song 
Acknowledging the Cheers of Participants in the Military Parade 
and One Million Strong Civilian Demonstration Celebrating the 
40th Anniversary of the Victory in the Fatherland Liberation 
War" and "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il-song on a Foreign Trip 
Receives a Bouquet Carrying the Best Wishes for His Longevity". 
  Chang-Chol, vice premier of the Administration Council and 
minister of culture and art, addressed the opening ceremony. 

</TEXT>

