<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spring Tree-Planting Season Under Way </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spring Tree-Planting Season Under Way </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1104102994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1006 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1104102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Spring tree-planting 
is in full swing throughout the country. 
  According to data available at the Forestry Management 
Department of the General Bureau of the Land Administration, 
nearly 200 million trees were planted across the country in 
recent 20 days. 
  Many counties of South Hwanghae Province and Kaesong and 
Nampo municipalities have already fulfilled their plans for 
spring tree-planting. 
  Korea has set the target to create 200,000 hectares of 
respective forests of oil-bearing trees and industrial trees in 
a few years and channelled big efforts to the work. 
  April, a good season for tree planting, was set as a 
tree-planting month and trees are planted through a social 
movement. 
  The nation's forests have been assigned to organs, 
enterprises and organizations and protected and managed by them 
with much care. 
  Afforestation in cities is being pushed ahead. 
  In recent years alone, thousands of hectares of forests have 
been created and a number of parks and recreation grounds built 
in major industrial and residential quarters. 
  In Pyongyang, more than 250,000 trees have already been 
planted in streets, residential quarters, parks and recreation 
grounds this year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

