<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets With IAEA Head Hans Blix </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With IAEA Head Hans Blix </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1204131694 Seoul KBS-1 Television Network in Korean 1231 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1204131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu met with Hans Blix, 
director-general of the International Atomic Energy Agency 
[IAEA], in Tokyo on 12 April. They shared the view that North 
Korea should allow an early additional inspection by the IAEA 
and again urged North Korea to allow inspections. 
  Minister Han, who arrived in Tokyo today on his way to 
Russia, urged the above during a one-hour talk with IAEA 
Director-General Hans Blix, who was visiting Japan. 

</TEXT>

