<H3> <TI>   Chinese Fishermen Rescued Off Cheju Island </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chinese Fishermen Rescued Off Cheju Island </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1204021094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0202 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1204021094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cheju, April 12 (YONHAP) -- The maritime police on 
Tuesday rescued eight crew members from a stranded Chinese 
fishing boat off the southwestern part of Cheju island, the 
Cheju Maritime Police said. 
  The maritime police said lifeboats were sent to waters off 
Mosulpo, Namcheju-kun, Cheju-do, around 8 A.M. to rescue Chinese 
fishermen from the vessel "Luyu 107," which ran aground earlier 
in the morning, the police said. 
  According to the police, the 80-ton fishing boat registered 
with Weihai City, Shandong Province, China, was swept away by 
high waves earlier in the morning while seeking a safe harbor in 
bad weather. Three of the 11 fishermen on the Luyu 107 had 
already swum to the port of Mosulpo, the police said. 

</TEXT>

