<H3> <TI>   President Approves Personnel Changes in Military </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Approves Personnel Changes in Military </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1204081594 Seoul YONHAP in English 0801 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1204081594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 12 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
approved military personnel changes explained Tuesday by Defense 
Minister Yi Pyong-tae, a government official said. 
  With the president's approval, the Defense Ministry is 
scheduled to announce its regular personnel changes at the end 
of this week or early next week. 
  The government plans to remove private organizations in the 
military through the personnel changes this month, but no 
details were available. 
  A senior government official said, "Defense Minister Yi 
briefed President Kim on the changes, but I have no information 
on personnel management concerning the generals and field grade 
officers who were members of 'Hana-hoe.'" 
  Hana-hoe was a private Army organization that counted former 
Presidents Chon Tu-hwan and No Tae-u among its members. 
  Another senior official said, "The overall feeling in the 
Army is that the personnel changes involving the Hana-hoe 
generals have not gone far enough. Most Army officers hope that 
all the Hana-hoe generals will be discharged or relieved of 
important posts." 

</TEXT>

