<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister To Meet U.S.' Kantor 15 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister To Meet U.S.' Kantor 15 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204101994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0955 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1204101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 12 KYODO -- Foreign Minister Tsutomu 
Hata will meet U.S. Trade Representative Mickey Kantor on Friday 
in Marrakech, Morocco, where they are attending a ministerial 
meeting of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT), 
government sources said Tuesday. Hata and Kantor will meet for 
about two hours over breakfast to seek a breakthrough in 
resuming the failed trade "framework" talks and also discuss 
multilateral issues, the sources said. 
  Relations between Tokyo and Washington have soured over 
trade 
following the collapse of the trade negotiations in February 
when Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa and U.S. President Bill 
Clinton met. 
  Hata's trip to Marrakech will formally be decided in a 
buck-slip cabinet meeting Wednesday morning, they said. 
  The foreign minister is to leave Japan on Wednesday noon for 
Morocco and return to Japan on Sunday, according to the sources. 
Hata was originally scheduled to leave Tuesday but was delayed 
due to the political turmoil following Hosokawa's sudden 
announcement last Friday that he will resign . 
  Hata, also deputy prime minister, is tipped as a strong 
candidate as the successor to Hosokawa. 
  On Monday, the Japanese Government sent Nobuo Matsunaga, the 
government representative for external economic affairs, to 
Marrakech in case Hata cannot attend the four-day GATT session 
that wraps up Friday. 
  Also in Marrakech, Hata will meet Australian Trade Minister 
Bob Mcmullan and Leon Brittan, the European Union's trade 
commissioner, separately Thursday, the sources said. 
  Hata may also meet U.S. Vice President Al Gore if possible, 
the sources said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

