<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["U.S. War Frenzy Undisguised" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- U.S. Secretary of 
State Christopher reportedly let out a war-reeking blast 
threatening the DPRK over the fictitious "nuclear issue". 
  In an interview with NBC April 10, Christopher, setting a 
deadline for the DPRK, told that "the diplomatic pressure on 
North Korea will give way to a more severe approach, with even a 
preemptive military strike not ruled out", unless the DPRK 
positively reacts to their one-sided and unjustifiable demand 
until that time. 
  U.S. Secretary of Defense William Perry, too, in an 
interview 
with NBC April 3 openly blared that "a preemptive military 
strike at North Korea will not be ruled out" and they were ready 
to risk a war. 
  Such war blasts ringing out continuously from among the U.S. 
high-ranking officials clearly show that the very one who seeks 
to provoke a war on the Korean peninsula is none other than the 
United States. 

</TEXT>

