<H3> <TI>   Deployment of U.S. Apache Helicopters Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deployment of U.S. Apache Helicopters Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1204104994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1043 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1204104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Calculated Dangerous Military Moves" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The Japanese ASAHI 
SHIMBUN reported that some latest attack helicopters Apache of 
the United States were deployed in a South Korean base on April 
10 for a "reinforcement of the combat power" of the U.S. Forces 
stationed in South Korea. 
  And the first batch of Patriot missile batteries which has 
left Texas will arrive in South Korea, timing to coincide with 
the Seoul trip of U.S. Secretary of Defense Perry in a few 
days, said the newspaper. 
  These are premeditated dangerous military moves to further 
destabilize the military situation on the Korean peninsula and, 
furthermore, to unleash another war. 
  As is known, the South Korean puppet clique have massively 
shipped in sophisticated weapons from the United States and 
"decided" to extend for an indefinite period the order to 
strengthen "the military posture of readiness" issued to the 
entire units of the puppet Army, which would cover the period 
from November last year to March this year. All the units of 
the three services of the puppet Army now are intensifying their 
"watch" to attack the North. 
  Such provocative moves of the U.S. imperialists and the 
South 
Korean trigger-happy elements for Northward invasion are based 
on their scrupulously worked out operational plans. 
  Already in September last year the Kim Yong-sam group 
completed a "New Operation Plan No. 5027" for northward invasion 
with the U.S. military officials and have staged war exercises 
against the North with the U.S. imperialists almost every day. 
  Facts vividly show that the ever more undisguised new war 
provocation moves of the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean 
puppet clique these days are an extension of their premeditated 
and intentional war moves stepped up from long ago. 
  Yet, the South Korean puppet clique are making quite a noise 
as if others were to blame for the tense situation on the Korean 
peninsula, raising a hue and cry over the fictitious 
"provocations" by the North. This is nothing but a despicable 
humbug for justifying their new war provocation moves. 
  The South Korean puppets are seeking to overpower the DPRK 
by 
"strength" in league with the U.S. imperialists and, 
furthermore, to gratify their wild ambition for "unification 
through Northward invasion" by force of arms, but it is a 
foolish daydream. 
  It is the unshakable will and policy of the DPRK to answer 
strength with strength, and dialogue with dialogue. 
  The U.S. imperialists and the "civilian" warmaniacs must 
ponder over things and stop acting rashly, looking squarely at 
the resolute will and determination of the Korean people who are 
fully prepared to cope with any event. 

</TEXT>

