  [Text] Cairo, April 12 KYODO -- Egypt's President Husni 
Mubarak is canceling a scheduled visit to Japan later this month 
because of the resignation of Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa, 
the Middle East News Agency reported Tuesday [12 April]. 
  Mubarak was scheduled to visit Japan as a state guest from 
April 18 to 21. 
  The Egyptian News Service said he will visit China starting 
April 21 as originally scheduled. 
  In Tokyo, a Foreign Ministry official said Japan has not 
received any official notice of the cancellation of Mubarak's 
visit. 

