  [Text] Seoul, April 8 (YONHAP) -- South Korea and Vietnam 
concluded a bilateral agreement on cooperation in the area of 
construction in Saigon Friday. 
  A Construction Ministry official said the agreement was 
signed by Construction Minister Kim U-sok now on a tour of 
Vietnam and his Vietnamese counterpart, Minister Ngo Xuan Loc. 
  The agreement calls for joint investment or joint projects 
