<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC Envoy Views Future of Bilateral Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Envoy Views Future of Bilateral Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204145694 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1155 GMT 12 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1204145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 12 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- In an 
interview to the "ARDYN ERH" correspondent the Ambassador of 
China to Mongolia Pei Jiayi has expressed his confidence in 
further development of goodneighbouring friendly relations 
between the two countries on the basis of efforts by both sides 
and the five principles of peaceful coexistence. He noted that 
for the development of Chinese-Mongolian relations in future of 
great significance would be the forthcoming visit by the premier 
of the State Council of the People's Republic of China (PRC) Li 
Peng to Mongolia at the invitation of the Prime Minister P. 
Jasray by the end of April in the current year. 
  Having expressed his satisfaction with the successful 
development of bilateral relations in all spheres, the 
ambassador stressed that there are not any substantial obstacles 
in this respect and as for the particular problems to be arising 
they would be solved gradually step by step. The ambassador 
said that the Chinese Government is taking strict measures for 
ill quality goods not to be penetrating into the international 
market. He also expressed a hope for gradual regulation of some 
certain problems concerning the barter trade connected in 
particular with the shortcomings of infrastructure and 
activities of the transport. 

</TEXT>

