<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK To Raise DPRK Rights Issues at World Forums </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1404115994 Seoul YONHAP in English 1150 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1404115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 14 (YONHAP) -- The government plans to 
raise from now on the question of North Koreans' human rights at 
international organizations, a senior government official said 
on Thursday. 
  The policy comes on heels of the recent government decision 
to handle the question of North Korean loggers in Russia from 
the approach of humanitarianism, that is, to explore ways to 
help them. 
  "The government is studying ways to grasp the comprehensive 
picture of North Koreans' human rights conditions including 
those of North Korean loggers in Russia," the official said. 
  Based on a finding, he said, the government will raise the 
issue at relevant United Nations agencies and world human rights 
organizations like the Amnesty International. 
  The official said the government may also in due course take 
steps to seek the repatriation of those South Korean fishermen 
and airplane crew persons being held in North Korea following 
their seizure by the North Koreans. 
  He further said he understands that a protest rally is being 
prepared in Osaka, Japan in connection with the recent missing 
of two Japanese women who, along with their Korean husbands, had 
moved to North Korea. 

</TEXT>

