<H3> <TI>   Contract Signed With PRC To Build Hotel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Contract Signed With PRC To Build Hotel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1404065494 Seoul YONHAP in English 0508 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1404065494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, April 14 (YONHAP) -- South Korea and 
China have signed a contract to build a hotel near Mt. Paekdu on 
a joint-venture basis, the semi-official China News Service 
reported Wednesday. 
  Mt. Paekdu is located on the border between North Korea and 
China and many South Koreans, who consider it a holy site, like 
to climb the mountain on the Chinese side. 
  Samson Enterprises Co. of Korea and Yanbian Tourism Corp. of 
Jilin Province have agreed to invest 8 million U.S. dollars in 
building a hotel to accommodate 1,200 guests near Mt. Paekdu. 
  The project has been approved by the Chinese State Council. 
  Samson and the Yanbian Tourism Company have set up a 
joint-venture company to operate the hotel over the coming 50 
years and they plan to use the profits to boost farming in 
Yanbian, largely populated by ethnic Koreans. 

</TEXT>

