<H3> <TI>   Tokyo Condemns Bus Bomb Attack in Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tokyo Condemns Bus Bomb Attack in Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1404094294 Tokyo KYODO in English 0931 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1404094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 14 KYODO -- Japan condemned Thursday 
[14 April] a bus bombing the previous day in Hadera, northern 
Israel, which killed at least six people and wounded about 30. 
  The Foreign Ministry said in a statement that the Japanese 
Government "strongly regrets" that civilians were victims in the 
attack and offered its sympathies to their families. 
  "Japan strongly condemns this kind of terrorism by some 
extremists, which is aimed at obstructing the peace process," 
the statement said. 
  Japan also regrets that Israel and the Palestine Liberation 
Organization (PLO) have not yet agreed on the withdrawal of 
Israeli troops from the Gaza Strip and West Bank town of Jericho 
despite an historic declaration on principles on self-rule last 
September in Washington. 
  The declaration stipulated the deadline for completion of 
the 
withdrawal as April 13. 
  Japan will continue to support the peace process, the 
statement said. 

</TEXT>

