  [Text] Tokyo, April 14 KYODO -- Japan's imports of 
table-use rice to deal with a poor rice crop in 1993 topped one 
million tons as of Wednesday, the Food Agency reported Thursday 
[13 April]. 
  It said the imports totaled 1,007,300 tons, comprising 
458,200 tons from Thailand, 325,200 tons from China, 175,900 
tons from the United States and 48,000 tons from Australia. 

