<H3> <TI>   Vice Ministers Seek Quick Government Formation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice Ministers Seek Quick Government Formation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1404025894 Tokyo KYODO in English 0230 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1404025894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 14 KYODO -- Parliamentary vice 
ministers on Thursday [14 April] urged the rapid formation of a 
new government, under the current coalition framework, to tackle 
a host of pressing political tasks, a government spokesman said. 
  They unanimously adopted, at their regular meeting, a 
resolution calling for the early installation of a new 
administration, Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary Yukio Hatoyama 
told a news conference. 
  The accord also calls for early Diet approval of the already 
overdue budget for fiscal 1994, which began April 1, Hatoyama 
said. 
  Parliamentary Vice Construction Minister Eisei Ito proposed 
that an agreement should be reached to end the political turmoil 
which has resulted from Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa's 
sudden decision to resign last Friday, he explained. 
  Hatoyama spoke of the need for the ruling parties to 
synchronize their basic policies, particularly on some issues of 
immediate concern, as a prerequisite for the formation of a new 
coalition government. 
  "Without such a policy consensus, the new government will 
face a crisis sooner or later," he said. 

</TEXT>

