BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 14 KYODO -- A cut in key lending rates 
by the German Bundesbank will stimulate Germany's economy and 
will be generally helpful for the world economy, a Bank of Japan 
(BOJ) source said Thursday [14 April]. 
  Japanese financial market sources expressed surprise at 
reports out of Frankfurt on the rate cut, but said the scale is 
small and unlikely to affect foreign exchanges. 
  In Frankfurt, the German central bank announced it will 
slash 
its discount rate to 5.00 percent from 5.25 percent per annum, 
and the Lombard rate to 6.50 percent from 6.75 percent per 
annum, effective from Friday. 

