<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Deployment of Military Airplanes Denounced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Deployment of Military Airplanes Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1304141894 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1300 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1304141894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1300 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to a military source, the U.S. 
imperialists on 10 and 11 April mobilized and deployed 20-odd 
military planes of various types in South Korea from overseas 
bases, thus committing a crime. 
  Formations of assault planes and pursuit-assault planes that 
took off from bases in Japan on 11 April flew into U.S. Air 
Force bases in South Korea. Prior to this, on 10 April, various 
types of military aircraft, including F-15, F-4, FA-18, AV-8 and 
EA-6, were mobilized and deployed to South Korea from U.S. bases 
in Japan and the Pacific area. 
  In addition, on 10 and 11 April, C-5 ultra-large strategic 
transport airplanes carrying a large number of troops and lethal 
equipment from bases on the U.S. mainland and the Pacific region 
and C-130 and C-141 transport airplanes landed in U.S. Air Force 
bases in South Korea and airlifted troops were mobilized and 
deployed to the operational zones and war equipment was supplied 
to these zones. 
  Our people and the People's Army are watching with vigilance 
the war preparation moves of the U.S. imperialists and the South 
Korean puppets. If the rascals perpetrate an act of aggression, 
we will deal a resolute punishment to them. 

</TEXT>

