<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1986 U.S. `Brutal Bombing Raid' on Libya Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1404105094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1019 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1404105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Cause of Libyan People Cannot Be Obliterated"--KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today in 
a signed article on the lapse of 8 years since the United States 
Bombed Libya says the United States cannot bring the Libyan 
people to their knees with any move. 
  The article goes on: 
  The brutal bombing raid on Libya by the United States in 
April 1986 brought to light the heinous nature of the United 
States which is committing undisguised terrorism under the 
pretext of "anti- terrorism". 
  The Libyan people are waging a brave struggle to consolidate 
the independence of the country and defend sovereignty against 
the aggression and intervention moves of the United States under 
the banner of anti-imperialist independence. Disliking this, 
the United States is taking issue with this country in a 
far-fetched way to find a pretext for new aggression and 
intervention. The U.S. vicious anti-Libya campaign is part of 
the systematic schemings to bring this country to its knees and 
turn the situation in this region in favour of the execution of 
its Africa policy. 
  Today the Libyan people are heightening vigilance against a 
possible new provocation of the United States. 
  The Korean people are extending firm solidarity for the 
Libyan people in their struggle to smash the threat and blockade 
moves of the imperialists and defend the national dignity and 
sovereignty. 
  The United States must stop its anti-Libya campaign. 

</TEXT>

