<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Australian Immigration Minister Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Australian Immigration Minister Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1304080994 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1304080994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nick Bolkus, minister of immigration and ethnic 
affairs of the Commonwealth of Australia, and his delegation 
arrived in Vientiane yesterday on an official and friendly visit 
to the Lao People's Democratic Republic [LPDR] at the invitation 
of LPDR Interior Minister A-sang Laoli. Nick Bolkus and his 
delegation were welcomed at Wattai Airport by Deputy Interior 
Minister Siangsom Kounlavong and a number of high-ranking 
Interior Ministry cadres. Also on hand at the airport to welcome 
the delegation was Michael Mann, ambassador extraordinary and 
plenipotentiary to the LPDR from the Commonwealth of Australia. 
  During the visit, Nick Bolkus is scheduled to pay a courtesy 
call on LPDR Deputy Prime Minister Khamphoui Keoboualapha. He 
will hold a meeting to exchange experiences with Interior 
Minister A-sang Laoli and will meet Khamtan Thepbouali, acting 
chairman of the Lao Front for National Construction. Nick 
Bolkus and his delegation are also scheduled to visit some 
historic and cultural sites in Vientaine Municipality and Luang 
Prabang Province. 

</TEXT>

