<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   SRV National Assembly Delegation Ends Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SRV National Assembly Delegation Ends Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1204104994 Vientiane KPL in English 0911 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1204104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, April 12 (KPL) -- A delegation of the 
Office of the National Assembly of the Socialist Republic of 
Vietnam led by Vu Mao, member of the CPV CC [Communist Party of 
Vietnam Central Committee], head of the Standing Committee and 
head of the Office of the National Assembly of the S.R. 
[Socialist Republic] of Vietnam left here for home on April 10 
ending its official visit since April 3 to the Lao PDR [People's 
Democratic Republic]. 
  During its 7 day visit to the country, the Vietnamese 
delegation had talks and signed a protocol with the Lao side 
which was led by Chaleun Yiapaoheu, member of the LPRP CC [Lao 
People's Revolutionary Party Central Committee], member of the 
Standing Committee of the National Assembly and head of the 
Office of the National Assembly of Laos. The Vietnamese 
delegation also called on Mr. Saman Vi-gnaket, Politburo member 
of the LPRP CC, and president of the National Assembly of Laos. 
  The delegation also visited Vientiane and Luang Prabang 
provinces where it saw a number of economic and cultural bases. 
  Seeing the delegation off at Wattai Airport were Mr. Chaleun 
Yiapaoheu and Vietnamese Ambassador to Laos, Mr. Bui Van Thanh 
and other high ranking officials of the National Assembly. 

</TEXT>

