<H3> <TI>   Press Reports on Fighting in Pailin Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Press Reports on Fighting in Pailin Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Battlefield Report: 12-13 Apr </H4>

<F P=102> BK1504013394 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1504013394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here is an additional report from the Pailin 
battlefield on 12 and 13 April. 
  1. The areas in and around Pailin: 
  On 12 April, we attacked and seized control of the general 
command post of the communist Vietnamese puppets and two-headed 
government at Boeng Pralit. Its commander fled back to Pailin. 
At 1400 on 12 April, we seized five enemy soldiers and two T-54 
tanks. 
  On the morning of 12 April, we fired at enemy trucks, 
damaging two of them and setting two others on fire in the 
southern part of Phnum Veng north of Route 10. 
  Also on 12 April, we set an oil tanker on fire in an area 
between Phnum Yat and O Ta Vau. 
  We still control O Rum-el and Ba Tang So. We have continued 
to attack Pailin with infantry forces and artillery fire. 
  2. On the eastern part of Pailin: 
  We set another military truck on fire, south of Phnum Srang 
hill adjacent to Phnum Veng. All troops on the truck were 
killed or wounded. 
  We continue to control Sala Krau. 
  Here is the situation on 13 April. The invading forces of 
the communist Vietnamese puppets and two-headed government have 
begun to collapse bit by bit. They have been plunged into 
confusion. The National Army of Democratic Kampuchea is 
attacking them from all directions. They have run out of 
ammunition, food, and medicine. Many of those who were killed or 
wounded were left scattered about. Nobody cares about anybody 
else. Their supply routes have been cut off completely for 
several consecutive days now. 

</TEXT>

