  [Text] Tokyo, April 15 KYODO -- A Canadian subsidiary of 
Nissan Motor Co. will take delivery of U.S.-built pickup trucks 
from Nissan Motor Manufacturing Corp. U.S.A. (NMMC) late this 
month, according to Nissan motor officials. 
  It will be the first time Nissan has exported U.S.-built 
pickup trucks to Canada. 
  NMMC is a U.S. manufacturing arm of the Japanese automaker. 
  Nissan said some 3,300 trucks will be shipped to Canada from 
NMMC in the business year that started on April 1. 

</TEXT>

